{
  "text": "On the screening visit, children underwent a standardized sputum induction procedure, utilized by the CF Therapeutic Development Network [CITATION_1] . Children inhaled 3% saline for 12 min using a DeVilbiss UltraNeb 99 nebulizer (Sunrise Medical, Somerset, PA). Bacterial and fungal cultures were carried out with any sputum obtained. If sputum was not expectorated, an oropharyngeal culture was obtained. None of the children spontaneously produced sputum at baseline.",
  "correct_citation": {
